Common Ways To Use:

1.Hair care:

For dry hair ends, mix 1/4 cup of fractionated coconut oil, 7 drops of Geranium oil, 7 drops of Lavender oil, and apply a few drops of this serum to damp hair just after a shower. Let dry completely without a hair dryer.

2.Bath:

When you feel sore all over, add 10 drops of Lavender essential oil, 5 drops of Peppermint essential oil, 5 drops of Orange essential oil, 1 tablespoon of Jojoba carrier oil, and a handful of Epsom salt into a water-filled bathtub, and sit inside for at least 15 minutes.

3.Perfume:

Mix, for example, 5 drops of Lavender essential oil, 4 drops of Orange essential oil, 1 drop of Ylang Ylang essential oil in a roller bottle, and fill it up with a carrier oil of your choice.

This essential oils variety pack is perfect for the home (bedroom, living room, bathroom, study room), office (workstation, conference room), outdoors, campground, yoga room, car, spa, and more!

For external use only. Not recommended for ingestion. Avoid contact with eyes. Keep out of reach of children. Keep away from pets. For topical use, first dilute essential oil with carrier oil. Item Name: Pete's Dragon VHS (2001) ‚Äì Disney Gold Collection
Description:
Relive the magic of Disney‚Äôs classic tale with this 2001 Gold Collection Edition VHS of Pete‚Äôs Dragon. Originally conceived in 1957 as a two-part episode for the Disneyland television series, the project was shelved and later revived as a feature film in 1975. Filming commenced in July 1976, with locations including a specially constructed lighthouse set in Morro Bay, California, and soundstages at Disney Studios in Burbank. The film premiered on November 3, 1977, blending live-action and animation to tell the heartwarming story of a young orphan, Pete, and his invisible dragon friend, Elliott. Featuring memorable performances by Helen Reddy and Mickey Rooney, this family-friendly musical adventure remains a nostalgic addition to any collection.
